EU Seeks Tougher Debt-Collection Rules, Handelsblatt Says

-- B y   T o n y   C z u c z k a
-- 
2011-07-25T06:51:47Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-25/eu-seeks-tougher-debt-collection-rules-handelsblatt-says.html
The European Union is proposing
measures to make it easier for companies to collect debts
throughout the EU, German newspaper  Handelsblatt  said, citing
European Commission documents.  The measures by EU Justice Commissioner  Viviane Reding ,
which require approval by the European Parliament and national
governments, include freezing accounts of debtors to help
companies get their money, the newspaper reported.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Tony Czuczka in Berlin at 
 aczuczka@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
James Hertling at  jhertling@bloomberg. 